IRS990.MissionDesc: THE OAKS OF DUNN COUNTY PROVIDES SUPPORTED LIVING TO SENIORS LIVING IN MENOMONIE, WI. THE FACILITY OFFERS SECURE, ACCESSIBLE, AND MAINTENANCE-FREE HOMES IN A HOUSING COMPLEX WITH COMMON SPACE AND BASIC SERVICES, INCLUDING TRANSPORTATION, WEEKLY HOUSEKEEPING, LAUNDRY SERVICES, PLANNED ACTIVITIES, AND A DAILY MAIN MEAL. THE OAKS OF DUNN COUNTY IS AN AFFILIATE OF MOSAIC. MOSAIC IS A FAITH-BASED ORGANIZATION SERVING PEOPLE WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES SO THAT ALL MAY REALIZE GOD'S GIFT OF WHOLENESS OF LIFE. WE ARE GUIDED BY THE PRINCIPLE THAT "EVERY INDIVIDUAL IS A PERSON OF WORTH." MOSAIC'S STAFF MEMBERS AND VOLUNTEERS PROVIDE INDIVIDUALIZED SERVICES, LIVING OPTIONS, WORK CHOICES, SPIRITUAL NURTURING, AND ADVOCACY TO APPROXIMATELY 4,900 INDIVIDUALS IN MORE THAN 700 COMMUNITIES ACROSS 13 STATES. INTERESTED PEOPLE CAN FIND MORE INFORMATION REGARDING THE OAKS OF DUNN COUNTY AT WWW.MOSAICINFO.ORG OR BY CALLING 715-235-7793.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDE RESIDENTIAL HOUSING AND SUPPORTED LIVING TO SENIORS. THE FACILITY OFFERS SECURE, ACCESSIBLE, AND MAINTENANCE-FREE HOMES IN A HOUSING COMPLEX WITH COMMON SPACE AND BASIC SERVICES, INCLUDING TRANSPORTATION, WEEKLY HOUSEKEEPING, LAUNDRY SERVICES, PLANNED ACTIVITIES, AND A DAILY MAIN MEAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S INTENDED USE OF THE TEMPORARILY RESTRICTED NET ASSETS IS FOR PROGRAM PURPOSES AS RESTRICTED BY THE DONORS.

MOSAIC RECOGNIZES THE EFFECT OF INCOME TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF THOSE POSITIONS ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED. SUCH TAX POSITIONS, WHICH ARE MORE THAN 50% LIKELY OF BEING REALIZED, ARE MEASURED AT THEIR HIGHEST VALUE. CHANGES IN RECOGNITION OR MEASUREMENT ARE REFLECTED IN THE PERIOD IN WHICH THE CHANGE IN JUDGMENT OCCURS. DURING 2023 AND 2022, MANAGEMENT DETERMINED THAT THERE ARE NO INCOME TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING RECOGNITION IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OTHER THAN DESCRIBED PREVIOUSLY.

THE SALARIES OF KRISTIN ROSSOW, STACY MORTON, CAROL MAU AND JULIE ZITTERGRUEN ARE PAID FROM A RELATED ORGANIZATION, MOSAIC. MOSAIC'S BOARD AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE USE AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT, A WRITTEN EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT, AND A COMPENSATION SURVEY IN ESTABLISHING THE COMPENSATION OF THE PRESIDENT AND CEO OF MOSAIC AND GUIDELINES FOR OTHER KEY STAFF.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE J, PART II, COLUMN C:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MOSAIC EVALUATES THE LIABILITY RELATED TO THEIR POSTRETIREMENT BENEFITS (SALARY AND HEALTH INSURANCE CONTINUATION) THROUGH AN ACTUARIAL REVIEW. THE ADJUSTMENT IS INCLUDED IN RETIREMENT AND OTHER DEFERRED COMPENSATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE MOSAIC BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPOINTS THE OAKS OF DUNN COUNTY'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE IS NO COMMITTEE WITH THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN OUTSIDE ACCOUNTING FIRM. IT IS REVIEWED BY THE TREASURER OF THE ORGANIZATION AND THEN SHARED WITH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH BOARD DIRECTOR COMPLETES A CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORM ANNUALLY AND SUBMITS IT TO THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE MOSAIC'S BOARD GOVERNANCE RISK AND INTEGRITY COMMITTEE. ANY FINANCIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ARE REPORTED TO THE TREASURER AND MOSAIC'S CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER FOR REPORTING ON THE FORM 990. ANY NEW CONFLICTS OF INTEREST THAT ARISE DURING THE YEAR ARE REQUIRED TO BE REPORTED AT THAT TIME.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OAKS OF DUNN COUNTY, INC. DOES NOT PAY COMPENSATION TO A CEO, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL, OFFICERS, OR ANY OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES. THEREFORE, A PROCESS FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION HAS NOT BEEN ESTABLISHED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INDIVIDUALS MAY REQUEST MOSAIC'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS THROUGH AN E-MAIL REQUEST FORM, WHICH IS AVAILABLE ON MOSAIC'S PUBLIC WEBSITE (WWW.MOSAICINFO.ORG).
THE BOARD ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT AND THE SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THIS PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
